    "description": "Hasegawa Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the retail and wholesale of Buddhist altars and accessories in Japan. It operates through Hasegawa Buddhist Altars and Buddhist Implements, Gravestones  Eastern Japan; Hasegawa Buddhist Altars and Buddhist Implements, Gravestones  Western Japan; Hasegawa Indoor Cemetery; Hasegawa Food & Beverage, Food & Miscellaneous Goods; Modern Buddhist Altars; and Other segments. The company also engages in the gravestone business comprising the sale of gravestones and tree burials; peaceful life support project business consisting of posthumous administration and identity guarantee, inheritance procedures, arrangement of belongings and real estate consultation, and supporting memorial services; operation of a dining and cafe business that sells food, as well as return food gifts for memorial services under the Tanomi brand; and indoor cemetery business, which includes the sale of indoor cemeteries owned by temples. In addition, it is involved in the sale of Buddhist altars and accessories on e-commerce sites; introduction of fixed ossuaries; and funeral consultation and introduction activities. The company serves Buddhist altar retailers. Hasegawa Co., Ltd. was founded in 1929 and is headquartered in Fukuoka City, Japan."
